<br>
So.. here's the breakdown<br>
<br>
1) Tashani is unresistable in PvP.. that reduces your MR by 90.  Even if you have a very high MR, the -90 MR will hurt you.  (50% bonus for debuff spells in PvP)  In order to resist mesmerise, you have to have a MR of around 100.  Which means base MR of 190.  There's your first advice.<br>
<br>
2) YOU CANNOT CHARM pets or PCs in PvP.  You cannot fear PCs in PvP either.  Chances are the enchanter will mesmerize your pet first, then tash / mez you after.  Most enchanters will have Rune on, so your first nukes will be eaten up by the absorb shield.<br>
<br>
3) Malosi line is resisted about 90% of the time against PCs with over 90 MR, so that is pretty much useless.<br>
<br>
4) If you cast annull magic on your opponent, while your pet is attacking it, your pet will kill itself, because it believes you are buffing your opponent.  EverQuest was not meant for PvP, so some of the glitches/bugs still exist<br>
<br>
Now that we got a basic idea of a PvP setup against an enchanter, here are some of the tips that you can use.<br>
-Sirrocco is a nasty AE, while the enchanter is busy mezzing the pet and Tashing you, get this spell off on him.  This will make him a) move and interrupt his casting, b) allows time for you to right click the Counteract Poison potion that you scored from your shaman friend.  Counteract Poison = no Tashani.<br>
-After that, use your fast cast time level 8 nuke to interrupt the enchanter cast, and keep doing it until the mesmerize on your pet is worn off. (You can use your metal golem wand to get rid of his buffs while you are at it as well)<br>
-Rinse and Repeat.<br>
<br>
So to summarize.. <br>
-Have your MR at least to 190 so you will surely resist Mesmerize even after Tashani<br>
-Have your level 8 spell loaded up to interrupt casting<br>
-Have Sirrocco loaded and use it wisely. (Pets will no longer get hit by your own AEs)<br>
-Kick some Enchanter booty <p>"So you think your kung-fu's pretty good, huh? I want to fight your brother... him.. against.. me.. LET'S KUNG-FOO!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unixomage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nixomage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(8/29/01 10:46:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: .</span><hr size=1> wear mr gear and lots of it..... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ublanafoflana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Blana Foflana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#333333>(10/25/01 9:33:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.eichenlaub.net/pictures/Blana-100,jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage vs Enchanter in duel</span><hr size=1> Hmm .. I really don't get it. Given, I only duelled one enchanter (42 mage against 45 ench) and not on a PvP server but we did it three times, he used different tactics and I won every time.<br>
<br>
- both starting with a pet and nuking: My 39 fire pet tears apart his 44 pet, attacks him, while he tries to get rid of the pet I nuke him down. A Mage nukes much harder and faster than an enchanter. (This was the closest of our encounters, I won with few HP left.)<br>
<br>
- I use fire pet, he no pet, tries to root, mezz and stuff ... actually he succeeded in rooting my pet and making me kill my own pet ... and still, he was so busy keeping things under control that he did not hurt me ... I got a few fast lvl 24 nukes on him though.<br>
<br>
- FFA in the arena, everyone running around and fighting like crazy ... easy, I'm used to solo and survive in crazy situation, he only knows his every day enchanter business.<br>
<br>
Where's the problem? <p>Blana Foflana,
